         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 117, recto: (1) Amenothes, son of Pamonthes, son of Panechates, has paid (2) to the bank of the northern [houses] for silver of poll of year 30, (3) among the men of Pikos, son of [Herwenenfer], 2 staters / (4) 1 stater / 2 staters again. Written in year 30, Mesore 20. (5) Likewise Mesore 27, 2 staters / 1 stater / 2 staters again.</ab>
